<h1>To John Forbes</h1>

<div class="docbody">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">Sir,</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">Camp (at night) 17th Novr 1758.</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>Colon. Bouquets letter came to my hands<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-06-02-0119-fn-0001" id="GEWN-02-06-02-0119-fn-0001-ptr">1</a> (just as the Bearer was passing by) from Colo. Armstrong.</p>
<p>I shall punctually observe all the directions contained thereinaltho I shall at the same time confess, I think it much safer and more elligible to have marched briskly on to our second Post, leaving the Road for Colo. Montgomery to open: We should by that means, have been as good as a covering-party to him, while we are fortifying a Camp which may be of great importance to the Army? Less time woud be lost by this means, and a straggling front (which ever will happen in expeditious cutting) would be avoidedbesides the advantage of (perhaps) getting into a secure camp before we might be discovered.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-06-02-0119-fn-0002" id="GEWN-02-06-02-0119-fn-0002-ptr">2</a></p>
<p>I have opened the Road between 7 &amp; 8 miles to-day, and am yet 3 miles short of Colo. Armstrong, who marched at 8 oclock.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-06-02-0119-fn-0003" id="GEWN-02-06-02-0119-fn-0003-ptr">3</a></p>
<span class="pb center" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-02-06-02-pb-0139">[139]</span>
<p>I understand by Captn Shelby, who is just come, from him, that Colo. Armstrong is not yet begun intrenching his Camp, which must again retard us to-morrow. Forwarding Provisions is highly necessaryhard labour consumes it fastbut all the men are in high spirits, and are anxious to get on. I shall be much pleased to see the Indians up; and am very glad to hear that Mr Croghan is so near at hand. The number with him is not mentionedI wish they were in our front also. I was extremely sorry to hear of your Indisposition to-day, being Sir, Your most obedient, and most humble Servt</p>
<div class="closer">
<p class="signed">G:W.</p>
</div>
<div class="postscript">
<p>To Genl Forbes.</p>   
</div>   
</div>
<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="GEWN-02-06-02-0119-sn">

   <p>
<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Letter Book Copy: letters copied into a bound letter-book ]">LB</abbr> (recopied), <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>.
</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-06-02-0119-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-06-02-0119-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>This letter is missing. See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-06-02-0116&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-06-02-0116-fn-0003#GEWN-02-06-02-0116-fn-0003" class="document">GW to Forbes, 17 Nov. 1758 (first letter), n.3</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-06-02-0119-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-06-02-0119-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>This paragraph and the second paragraph of <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-06-02-0123" class="document">GW to Forbes, 18 Nov.</a>, suggest that Bouquets missing letter (see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-06-02-0119&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-06-02-0119-fn-0001#GEWN-02-06-02-0119-fn-0001" class="document">note 1</a>) altered his instructions of 16 Nov., which were for GW, upon Col. Archibald Montgomerys arrival at Armstrongs New Camp, to march wth a Sufficient force to the heads of Turtle Creek where you [will build a] Campleaving to Col. Montgomerys Brigade the Road to cut to you. The letter that GW got from Forbes on 18 Nov., which is also missing, evidently reaffirmed Bouquets original instructions for GW to proceed immediately to Turtle Creek and build there the second fortified encampment for the advancing army, leaving it to the Highlanders to cut the road from New Camp.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-06-02-0119-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-02-06-02-0119-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>For the probable site of GWs camp the night of 16 Nov., see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-06-02-0113&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-06-02-0113-fn-0001#GEWN-02-06-02-0113-fn-0001" class="document">Orderly Book, 16 Nov., n.1</a>. For the site of John Armstrongs New Camp, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-06-02-0121&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-06-02-0121-fn-0001#GEWN-02-06-02-0121-fn-0001" class="document">Orderly Book, 18 Nov., n.1</a>.</p>

</div>
